metadata.name: Meridian #15
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Meridian' attempts to capture some of the beauty and simplicity of Bauhaus design ideas. The addition of a line (or Meridian) to these simple shapes creates a colorful, striking design with an Art Deco vibe!

To download:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x2000px PNG.

metadata.name: Isomeric doppelgangers #49
metadata.description:
'Isomeric doppelgangers' 

Spatial isomerism, is a form of isomerism in which molecules have the same molecular formula and sequence of bonded atoms (constitution), but differ in the three-dimensional orientations of their atoms in space.

This artworks flips several boxes on the X or Y axis, resulting in two gemelar images, each with the same palette but a different color mix. The perception of diverse scenes is based only on these modifications.

The collection is limited to 100 works of art.

-----

Press 's' to save the current canvas view.

-----

Features:

Palette: coral, gray, retro, vrolik3, origami, sooph, jfa, bell
Zoom: low, medium, high, random
Orientation: portrait, vertical
Fill: true, false


-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.description:

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #485
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: CR Art Sessions //2 #292
metadata.description:
Grayscale, Hold the Line, and Mondrian walk into a bar. The bartender looks up and says, "What is this, some kind of art project?"

Grayscale responds, "No, we're just here for a drink."

Hold the Line adds, "But we can definitely add some color to the place if you want."

Mondrian chimes in, "I prefer to keep things simple and stick to the basics."

The bartender shakes his head and says, "I'll be the judge of that. What can I get you all?"

Grayscale orders a Guinness, Hold the Line asks for a gin and tonic, and Mondrian asks for a glass of white wine.

The bartender serves up the drinks and says, "That will be $15.50, please."

Grayscale pulls out a twenty-dollar bill and hands it to the bartender, saying, "Keep the change."

The bartender thanks him and says, "Thanks, Grayscale. You always know how to liven up the place."

Hold the Line raises his glass and says, "Cheers to that!"

Mondrian nods and clinks glasses with the others, and the three of them enjoy their drinks and the rest of their evening at the bar.

-----

Press "e" to save a png (3240*4500 or 4500*3240 px) while in live mode.

-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr (2022)

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #124
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).
